it turns out old mugs of tea, toothpaste-encrusted bathrooms and mouldy food are among the top 'cleaning sins' committed by busy Brits. A study by Krcher has revealed six in ten Brits are too busy to clean their homes. A study of 2,000 people by cleaning equipment company, Krcher, revealed that a whopping six in ten full-time working Brits are too busy to clean their homes each week.